        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>2941 Groveland ave<lb/>
                Chicago Sep. 12. 1888.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Mr. Mora&#239;s&#44;&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>If you know<lb/> my reverence and admiration for<lb/> you&#44; you would value the<lb/> pleasure I had to receive your<lb/> card&#44; of New&#45;Year&#44; you<lb/> kindly sent me.  It was a<lb/> delightful surprise&#44; and<lb/> those kind wishes written<lb/> of your own hand&#44; are<lb/> for me&#44; as a blessing of<lb/> God&#44; to us&#44; on this new<lb/> Roshashanah.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I <sic>I</sic> had good news of<lb/> you all through Mrs. D&#39;Ancona.<lb/>  Her greatest joy in coming to<lb/> Philadelphia&#44; was to see you<lb/> and your family as long as<lb/> possible&#44; Imagine her regrets<lb/> and <sic>disapointment</sic>&#44; to be<lb/> so indisposed&#44; that all<lb/> her anticipations <sic>dissapeared</sic><lb/> counne des ch&#226;teaux d&#39;Espagne.<lb/></p>
            <p>Weekly I hear of<lb/> you through Josephine&#44;<lb/> Once more&#44; love&#44; is going to<lb/> take a captive&#44; among your<lb/> dear ones.  Do not think<lb/> dear friend that one more<lb/> goes&#44; on the contrary you<lb/> gain 2 more children&#44;<lb/> your family circle is<lb/> getting larger&#44; in number<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>of hearts to love and be<lb/> devoted to you.  God&#39;s laws<lb/> are not always uniform with<lb/> us mortals wishes.  But he<lb/> has been kind to you&#44; in<lb/> surrounding you for so<lb/> long&#44; with a lovely&#44; healthy<lb/> family&#44; whose only sorrow<lb/> they give you&#44; is to follow<lb/> the natural law&#44; of<lb/> submitting sooner or later<lb/> to the very powerful<lb/> King Cupid.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear husband<lb/> was so happy&#44; by your<lb/> thoughtful attention&#44; and<lb/> wishes me to tender you<lb/> his very best regards.  We<lb/> are all well and happy.<lb/>  Thank God&#44; and my<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p><sic>my</sic> little Graciella&#44; the<lb/> joy and Sunshine of the<lb/> house.  I trust&#44; I may soon<lb/> bring her east&#44; and you may<lb/> kiss her picturesquely lovely<lb/> face.<lb/></p>
            <p>Before closing my letter&#44;<lb/> accept my best wishes for<lb/> the coming holyday&#44; so great<lb/> and sacred&#44; and trust you may<lb/> stand in good health&#44; its<lb/> hardship.<lb/></p>
            <p>A kiss for me to all<lb/> the dear girls&#44; and to you.<lb/>  l&#39;expression de mon affection<lb/> la plus Sincere<lb/> Votre jenne amie deb&#39;ou&#233;e<lb/> Hermine Jacoby<lb/></p>
            </body>
